thoughtless /ˈθɔːtlɪs/

1. ADJ If you describe someone as thoughtless , you are critical of them because they forget or ignore other people's wants, needs, or feelings. 不顾及他人的 [表不满] 

例： ...a small minority of thoughtless and inconsiderate people. …一小撮不顾及别人、不替别人着想的人。 

例： It was a thoughtless remark and I regretted it immediately. 这是一句欠考虑的话，我马上就后悔了。 

2. thoughtlessly ADV 不顾及他人地 [ADV with v] 

例： They thoughtlessly planned a picnic without him. 他们考虑不周，安排了一次野餐却没带上他。

